<%# Locals: automation (hash with :automated_conversations) %>
<%# Hidden when all counts are zero — caller guards this, but we exit early too. %>
<% return if automation[:automated_conversations].to_i == 0 %>

<div class="card-solid grow w-full">
  <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-500">
    <%= t("dashboard.automation.title") %>
  </h2>

  <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
    <%= t("dashboard.automation.conversations_html",
          count: tag.span(automation[:automated_conversations], class: "font-mono tabular-nums text-deep")) %>
  </p>

  <%#
    TODO(anella-automation-receipts): expand this card when the following are instrumented.

    1. Auto-confirmed appointments
       - Requires AuditLog event_type "appointment.auto_confirmed" emitted from the
         confirmation flow (wherever Anella flips a pending appointment without human action).
       - Query: space.audit_logs.where(event_type: "appointment.auto_confirmed",
                created_at: week_start..week_end).count

    2. Reminders sent
       - Requires either an AuditLog event_type "message.reminder_sent" or a dedicated
         MessageDelivery model distinguishing reminders from other template sends.
       - Today, message credits are deducted at send time but the purpose (reminder vs
         booking confirmation vs manual broadcast) is not stored per send.

    3. Inbox auto-replies
       - Covered partially by automated_conversations; granular "N auto-replies sent"
         would need per-message tracking.

    Until these land, the card renders a single line and no placeholder numbers.
  %>
</div>
